Measurements were made relative to monitor cross

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The cross sections measured in this work
have maximum errors of of mostly up to 10%, though in
a few cases the errors are larger. The major sources
* the uncertainties in the determination of
the 2 % uncertainty in the  relative photopeak
* the uncertainty in determining the Compton
background, particularly in the case of complex
* The errors arising from uncertainties in weighing
and mixing the samples, timings, self-absorption of
gamma-rays, and statistics have also been taken into
! The errors arising from uncertainties in decay
schemes are not included. These should, however be
small because in most of the present investigations
strong gamma-rays with fairly well-known decay
monitor cross sections added to subworks.
